  "texts": [
    "I show that the generation of invalid outputs provides a self-corrective mechanism that filters low-likelihood samples from the language model output.",
    "Conversely, enforcing valid outputs produces structural biases in the generated molecules, impairing distribution learning and limiting generalization to unseen chemical space.",
    "Together, these results refute the prevailing assumption that invalid SMILES are a shortcoming of chemical language models and reframe them as a feature, not a bug.",
    "Over the past century, more than 100 million small molecules have been synthesized in the search for new drugs and materials 1.",
    "These efforts have explored only an infinitesimal subset of chemical space, the size of which is estimated at over 10 60 molecules 2."
  ],
